      <div>
        <p class="max-w-prose font-manrope pl-5">
          The work Minuet is based on a painting by the Italian Rococo painter
          Giovanni Domenico Tiepolo. The painting, which hangs in the Louvre in
          Paris, depicts a dancing couple surrounded by masked spectators. The
          title, Minuet, refers specifically to a special, elegant dance for
          couples that dominated the aristocratic ballrooms of Europe from ca.
          1650–1750. <br /> In the work, Yukhnovich has also incorporated figures
          from the French Rococo painter Antoine Watteau’s depictions of commedia
          dell’arte. Commedia dell’arte is an Italian theatre form that originated
          in the 16th century and is characterised by improvisation, comedic characters
          and masked figures such as Harlequin, Pierrot and Columbine.
        </p>
